															<br />
															<p align="left">The Exploration & Production Technology Institute (EPTI) is KNOC's internal research arm founded in January 2006. Its founding purpose is to achieve technology independence and secure technologies for development of non-conventional resources to better support Korea’s oil and gas development projects at home and abroad.</p>
															<br />
															<p align="left">The members of the EPTI have expertise in diverse areas such as geology, geophysics, and resource engineering as well as experience and knowhow in domestic and overseas oil fields. They are involved in mid- to long-term research projects in such specialized areas as basin analysis in prospective regions; processing and analysis of geophysical exploration data; development, production, and drilling methods for shale gas and gas hydrates; and CO2 storage technologies as well as technology development projects in close connection with operation sites.</p>
															<br />
															<p align="left">We at the EPTI will do our best to help create a cooperative ecosystem for the country’s petroleum businesses so that they can utilize not only the technologies and knowhow we ourselves develop internally but those obtained from joint research with other companies and universities and partnerships with major oil companies overseas for their operation sites. In so doing, we will advance the institute’s technologies to the global level, thereby contributing to the realization of the vision of KNOC as the state-run oil company.</p>
